references.paper_title: SDXL: Improving latent diffusion models for high-resolution image synthesis
references.reason: This paper is crucial as it introduces SDXL, which is the base text-to-image diffusion model primarily used for logo insertion and experiments in the silent branding attack.

references.paper_title: High-resolution image synthesis with latent diffusion models
references.reason: This paper is fundamental as it presents Latent Diffusion Models, the foundation of the text-to-image generation approach.

references.paper_title: Dreambooth: Fine tuning text-to-image diffusion models for subject-driven generation
references.reason: This paper is essential because DreamBooth is used for logo personalization, enabling the model to generate specific logos effectively.

references.paper_title: Nightshade: Prompt-specific poisoning attacks on text-to-image generative models
references.reason: This paper is highly relevant as it explores data poisoning attacks on text-to-image models, providing a baseline for comparison and highlighting the vulnerabilities in this domain.
This paper is significant as it introduces OWLv2, which is used for logo detection during the mask generation stage, a critical step in the automated poisoning algorithm.
